       	== Shriyaa Mittal, PhD
	\n
	2024 - Present | Scientific Editor | Cell Press

	\n
	2022 - 2024 | Journal Manager | [https://publishing.aip.org/ AIP Publishing]
	\n
	Managed the launch of four open access journals.

	\n
	2020 - 2022 | Postdoctoral researcher | Harvard Medical School\/Massachusetts General Hospital
	\n	
	Investigated structural dynamics of RNA and its implications towards our understanding of the origins of life in the [https://molbio.mgh.harvard.edu/szostakweb/ laboratory of Jack W. Szostak].

	\n
	2015 - 2020 | PhD in Biophysics \& Quantitative Biology | University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign

	\n
	2010 - 2015 | Bachelors in Computer Science \& Masters in Computational Natural Science | [http://iiit.ac.in/ IIIT, Hyderabad], India
#	I am a Scientific Editor at Cell Press.

#	Before this, I was a Journal Manager at [https://publishing.aip.org/ AIP Publishing] where I managed the launch of four open access journals including /APL Machine Learning/, /APL Quantum/, /APL Electronic Devices/, and /APL Energy/.

#Prior to embarking on an editorial career, I was a postdoctoral researcher in the [https://molbio.mgh.harvard.edu/szostakweb/ laboratory of Jack W. Szostak] at Harvard Medical School\/Massachusetts General Hospital\/HHMI. My research focused on investigating molecular mechanisms of RNA and their implications towards our understanding of the origins of life. 

#	I received my PhD in Biophysics from the University of Illinois, Urbana-Champaign working with [http://www.shuklagroup.org/diwakar-shukla/ Prof. Diwakar Shukla] studying membrane transporter proteins using computational methods. I got my Bachelors in Computer Science and Masters in Computational Natural Science at [http://iiit.ac.in/ IIIT, Hyderabad], India.

